HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 406
BY REPRESENTATIVE FREEMAN
CONDOLENCES: Expresses the condolences of the House of Representatives on the death
of Adelaide Wisdom Benjamin
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To express the condolences of the House of Representatives on the death of Adelaide
3 Wisdom Benjamin.
4 WHEREAS, it is with immense sadness and profound regret that the House of
5 Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana has learned of the passing, on May 30, 2026,
6 of Adelaide Wisdom Benjamin; and
7 WHEREAS, Adelaide Wisdom Benjamin was born in New Orleans, Louisiana, to
8 William Bell Wisdom and Mary Freeman Wisdom and raised to understand the importance
9 of community involvement; and
10 WHEREAS, Ms. Benjamin graduated from Louise S. McGehee School and enrolled
11 at Hollins College; after two years, she returned home and enrolled at Newcomb College,
12 where she graduated in 1954; during this period of her life, she reigned as the Krewe of Rex
13 queen on Mardi Gras night; she then earned a law degree at Tulane University School of
14 Law; and
15 WHEREAS, after completing law school, Ms. Benjamin joined the firm of Wisdom,
16 Stone, Pigman, and Benjamin and practiced law from 1956 to 1958; she married Edward
17 Benjamin and retired from practicing law to focus on raising a family; she graduated from
